This indicates that $\alpha$ governs the weighting between the most recent parameter update ($[w]^{k-1}$) and the one from two steps prior ($[w]^{k-2}$). This is characteristic of a momentum-based smoothing technique, where $\alpha$ determines how much weight is given to the recent update versus the older one.

