On Page 4, the text discusses Independent-APC (IAPC) and mentions: “However, its performance degrades significantly when evaluated on unseen attacks. This suggests that training with a single attack leads to overfitting and hinders generalization across diverse attack patterns.” To alleviate this limitation, the paper adopts a hybrid training strategy, training APC jointly on adversarial examples generated from multiple attack types.

This indicates that APC trades off data efficiency (by requiring adversarial examples from multiple attack types during training) for robustness (to generalize across diverse attacks). The paper addresses this by using a hybrid training strategy that exposes APC to heterogeneous attack patterns.

